casebody.data:
First Department,

April, 1977

(April 5, 1977) Dina M. Viscarde, Petitioner, v State Human Rights Appeal Board et al., Respondents.

Application, pursuant to section 298 of the Executive Law, unanimously denied, the cross motion granted and the petition dismissed, without costs and without disbursements. If not dismissed, the determination would be confirmed on the merits. No opinion. Concur—Murphy, P. J., Birns, Capozzoli and Lane, JJ.
